Geometry: Feasible POC at R = 0.04–0.05 m (major radius), a = 0.008–0.01 m (minor) for ~8–10 cm toroid diameter.
Mass Bleed: ~10¹⁷–10¹⁸ atoms/s (xenon) via gated injector to maintain n = 10²⁰ m⁻³.
Code Repo Section: See /simulations/bootstrap_model.py for full script (includes parametric sweeps for η, R, etc.).

Prototype Development PlanRoadmap emphasizes iterative, safe builds from desktop POC to scaled applications. Focus on feasible sizes (cm-scale for visibility/stability).Phase 1: Desktop Stable Vortex Prototype (Current)Goal: Visible helical flow, axial region, >10–30 s autonomous lifetime in closed vessel.
Hardware:Vessel: 20–30 cm quartz/borosilicate chamber (~$200–500, e.g., Chemglass CG-124-02).
Gas: Xenon/neon mix at 1–10 Torr (rotary pump evacuation).
Drive: Hybrid RF (12–15 MHz coil, 5–10 turns copper, ~100–500 W) + axial laser (532 nm CW diode, 1–5 W, focused ~1 mm beam).
Fields: External B = 0.015–0.045 T (neodymium coils); self-field target 0.08–0.25 T.
Diagnostics: EM probe (8–18 MHz), optical pyrometry (T monitoring), camera for helical flow.

Build Steps:Assemble vessel with RF coil external, laser port axial.
Evacuate, fill gas, apply RF to initiate plasma.
Ramp to threshold: Monitor EM shift to self-modes.
Introduce gated bleed (piezo valve, 1–10 mg/s pulses) for sustainment.

Test Protocol:Ramp RF power; log T, γ (inferred from f), lifetime.
Verify bootstrap: Cut external inputs; check persistence.
