Troubleshooting: Dissipation? Increase axial feed. Unstable? Tune poloidal twist via B_ext.

Safety Checklist (Critical—HV/RF/laser/plasma pose lethal risks):Use insulated gloves, grounded enclosures, HV interlocks.
Laser: Class 4 goggles, beam stops.
Plasma: UV shielding, ozone ventilation.
Always discharge capacitors before handling.

Phase 2: Benchtop Arc/SGTC IntegrationScale to higher power: Spark Gap Tesla Coil (SGTC) for initial arc, transition to stable toroid.
Add partial enclosure for humidity/mass bleed.

Phase 3: Lightning Capture + Fist-Sized UnitOutdoor tests: Capture natural discharges to charge vortex.
Optimize to R ≈ 0.05–0.1 m for portable "fist-sized" cell.

Phase 4: ApplicationsIntegrate: Tesla EV battery swap, Starship auxiliary power.
Open-source all designs for community refinement.

